  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a 4-byte tag used to identify OpenType and TrueType font tables and variation axes.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

<xref:T:SkiaSharp.SKFourByteTag> is a compact, value-type representation of the 4-byte identifiers used throughout the OpenType specification to name font tables (e.g., `name`, `cmap`, `GSUB`) and variable font axes (e.g., `wght`, `wdth`, `ital`).

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from characters
var wght = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Parse from string
var tag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght");

// Round-trip to/from uint
uint raw = tag;
SKFourByteTag restored = raw;

Console.WriteLine(tag.ToString()); // "wght"
```
]]></format></remarks>
